# ===========================================
# SharePoint Configuration
# ===========================================
# These environment variables are required for SharePoint integration.
# Follow the steps below to obtain these values from Azure Portal.

# Azure AD Tenant ID
# Find in: Azure Portal > Azure Active Directory > Overview > Tenant ID
SHAREPOINT_TENANT_ID=your-tenant-id-here

# Azure AD Application (Client) ID  
# Find in: Azure Portal > App registrations > Your App > Overview > Application (client) ID
SHAREPOINT_CLIENT_ID=your-client-id-here

# Azure AD Client Secret
# Create in: Azure Portal > App registrations > Your App > Certificates & secrets > New client secret
SHAREPOINT_CLIENT_SECRET=your-client-secret-here

# SharePoint Site URL
# The full URL to your SharePoint site (e.g., https://yourtenant.sharepoint.com/sites/yoursite)
SHAREPOINT_SITE_URL=https://yourtenant.sharepoint.com/sites/yoursite

# SharePoint Drive ID (Optional)
# If you want to target a specific document library, provide its drive ID
# Leave empty to use the default document library
SHAREPOINT_DRIVE_ID=

# ===========================================
# Setup Instructions
# ===========================================
#
# 1. Register an App in Azure AD:
#    - Go to Azure Portal (https://portal.azure.com)
#    - Navigate to Azure Active Directory > App registrations
#    - Click "New registration"
#    - Name: Your App Name
#    - Supported account types: Single tenant (this organization only)
#    - Click "Register"
#
# 2. Configure API Permissions:
#    - Go to your app > API permissions
#    - Click "Add a permission"
#    - Select "Microsoft Graph"
#    - Choose "Application permissions" (not Delegated)
#    - Add the following permissions:
#      * Sites.Read.All (to read SharePoint sites)
#      * Sites.ReadWrite.All (to read/write SharePoint sites)
#      * Files.Read.All (to read files)
#      * Files.ReadWrite.All (to read/write files)
#    - Click "Grant admin consent" (requires admin permissions)
#
# 3. Create Client Secret:
#    - Go to your app > Certificates & secrets
#    - Click "New client secret"
#    - Add a description and select expiry
#    - Copy the secret VALUE immediately (it won't be shown again)
#
# 4. Get Tenant ID:
#    - Go to Azure Active Directory > Overview
#    - Copy the "Tenant ID"
#
# 5. Get Client ID:
#    - Go to your app > Overview
#    - Copy the "Application (client) ID"
#
# 6. Get Site URL:
#    - Navigate to your SharePoint site in a browser
#    - Copy the URL (e.g., https://contoso.sharepoint.com/sites/mysite)
